,» By Alice Rogoii
What do a bicycle-repair
course, a Marxism study group,
And a poetry workshop have in
common? Each one is is current offering in the Grinnell
"curriculum" 1. ii a t Students
won’t find listed in their categories. Instead, they are part
of a new Grinnell phenomenon
known as the Free University.
The Free University is actually an otishuot of a committee
organized to discuss education.
Freshman Chris Freeberg and
some of his friends concluded
that many or Grinnell’s exciting contributions to a “class—
less society“ (are, outside of
class) were going unheralded
ﬁnd intended. They also felt
that interested students should
be encouraged to get together
and to share their time and
parents with one another.
If anyone has a suggestion
for a new nonprofit study group
that they would like to lead or
to participate in, the Free University state will act as a CDol'creating committee to organize and ‘publicity the activity.
The Free University, therefore, serves as an information
center that united and initiated
Such activities.
Groups already in operation
Include an Eastern philippines
discussion group and the Guerllla Theater. A Cooking Class ls
