Actor 'n-Residence los lead Role in Folkslllger Pele seeker placed for Concert Tuesday
Six Characters in Search of an Author
William Late, who plays a
leading role ill the Grinnell College Theatre production of
Luigi Pirandello's “Six Characters in Search of an Author,"
was a member of the U.S.
Diplomatic Corps before beginning a career in the theatre.
“Six Characters in Search of
an Author" will be presented
at 3 pm, tonight and tomorrow
in ARH Auditorium as part of
Homecoming—Parents' Weekend
activities.
William Ball’s off-Broadway
removal in 1963 started renewal interest in “Six Characters
in Search of an Author," Considered a classic work from one
of the most residential of the
early voices of modem theatre,
the always kitty and sometimes
proposed play simultaneously
tells a story and asks what is
meant by theatre.
Laie, a member of the Mile
walker directory Theatre
company who is an actor-in—
residence here this semester,
holds a BA. degree from tunisia College, an MA. from the
University oi Pittsburgh, and
an M.F.A, from the New York
University School of Drama.
Among the Milwaukee directory Theatre productions he
has appeared in are “The Skin
of Our Teeth,” ”fully,” “The
Imaginary Invalid,” “The Three
Sisters," and “sarah/made."
He has also appeared at the
Theatre L’tommy Dieu in
Alexandria, Minn, and the
Charles warehouse in Boston,
“Six Characters in Search of
an Author," which also includes a cast of 11 students, is
being directed by Porter St
Woods of the theatre faculty.
James E. needed Iii, also or
the theatre faculty, designed
and constructed the set.
